{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_sierra_ver02/data/sn84026749/100492635/1908051701/0095.xml":{"full_text":"HARRIMAN HOPEFUL\nAT TRADE OUTLOOK\nRailrcadsAble to Get Money.\nOut of Politics and Avoids\nOfficial Calls.\n\n\n\n\n'E. H, Harriman, master of a railroad\nmileage that would span the globe,\ndropped into Washington to attend a din\nTied \u00bbnd before his departure yesterday\ndeclared that prosperty was on its way\nback, and would get here just about in\nproportion as the people returned to\nsound, sensible understanding of busi\nness condition. He expressed the con\nfident conviction that there is a much\nmore comfortable feeling as a result\nof recent court decisions, which have\nconvinced the community that the courts\nmay yet be relied upon to protect the\nrights of the people, and insisted that\nthe financial troubles are at an end so\nfar as concerns the railroads. He said:\n\n\n\nHoy.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nI\nwo\n\n\n\n\n\u201cThe feeling is easier, and all the\ncountry needs now is to be let alone\u2014\nless\u2019 agitation, excitement. Ii has be\ncome apparent of late that agitation has\nceased to have so much effect on the\npublic mind. The people are geiling\nback to a calmer frame, confidence that\nthe courts will protect rights and inter\nests and persons has been inspired by\nSome recent decisions. There has been\naltogether too much unrest\u2014I don\u2019t\nmean on the part of anybody in par\nticular, but among the whole people.\n\n\n|E\nPAE\n\n|E\nO58\nWe are getting \"back to better condi\ntions\n\u201cThe business outlook? There has not\nbeen a spring in many years when the\nprospect for crops was better than now.\nThe farmer felt the recent financial\ntroubles less than anybody else. He has\nbeen making so much money in recent\nyears, paid his debts, and has money\nin the banks. The banks in agricultural\ndistricts were stronger in reserve than\n\n\n\n\n5\nB\n\ni Ee)\nBB he\n90c 68-inch\nWhite Organdy,\ni\n=a 3\n\nLgl?\n\n23c\nExtra width (88\ninch)