ese\u2014I'm sure I don\u2019t know of\nit\u2014for which unduly high rates are\ncharged they should be adjusted. But\nI don\u2019t know about the discussion of in\ncreasing rats.\u2019\n\u201cAnd about politics, Mr. Harriman?\u201d\n\u201c0, I'm\u2014I was going te say I'm out of\nthat; but I really never was in it. I\ndon\u2019t know anything about politics and\ndon\u2019t expect to.\u201d\n\u201cDon\u2019t expect to finance any cam\npaigns this year, then?\u201d\n\u201c0, now, I never did that: not reaily,\nvou know. I claim the right to use my\nown in my own way; I have that rigit,\ndon't you think?\u201d\nThe interviewer assured Mr. Harriman\nthat here in Washington there is a\nwidespread impression that it would be\nuseless to attempt to enforce any other\npolicy on Mr, Harrignan.\n1 1 5\n\u201cWil! you call on any public officials\nwhile here?\u201d\n\u201cNo, none: I've done with all thal.\u201d\nRates Should Be Reasonabie.\nOut of Politics.\nA Lot of 85 Dozen Children\u2019s 1 4\n25\u00a2 Gauze Undershirts C\nBest of \u201clite Gauze Shirts for children up to 16\nears, of th: finest combed Eg ptian\n|B\nyara; 3 pearl button front; long or short\nsleeves, ribbed cufis. Others get 25\u00a2 for [4p\nthese garments. Job price\nCE EE EE EEE\nSLASHED WAIST PRICES\n5c WAISTS 47 ic\nNew Peter Pan or Stylish Pleated Waists, of plain\nblue or fancy ginghams, black satines, white corded\nmadaras\ni\nt (open front, long sleeves) or fine white\niinen waists withentire fronts of fine embroid- 5\nery; values up to we, Special\n47\n\u00abvives asumans\n69 for Waists worth up to $1.49\nFine Persian Lawn Waists] with entire full fronts of\nmost expensive of eyelet and blind Swiss all-over\n3\ne\nhroidery. Opel front or back. Youn can't\net better elesewhere for 98 and bind than\nhere for\nEEE EE ETE TE LE LTT ae Sree an an\n$3.00 Jop Silk Waists, $i. 69\nBest of Wash Fly Waists in black and white, hand\nsome trimmings \u2018ne lace and lace\nmedallions: French tucked button 