ons of Dr. Alexander and\nAssistant Give Rise to Sensa\ntional Story.\nBRISTOL, Tenn., May 16.\u2014-Dr, E, C.\nAlexander, chief surgeon at the Nation\nal Soldiers\u2019 Home at Johnson City, one\nof the largest in the couniry, and his\nassistant, Dr. T. B. HugheS, have re\nsigned suddenly.\nThere is a sensational story in con\nnection with their resignations, which\nhas not yet been officially confirmed.\njovernor Sm:th, of the home, refuses 0\ndiscuss the matter.\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES, SUNDAY, MAY 17, 1908.\nDANCES TO DEATH\nIN LONELY WHIRL\nRich Frenchman's Daughter Had\nMania Since Child\nni TR\nPARIS, May I\u00bb \u2014\u201cDance-mania\u201d has\ncaused the death >f Valentine Taravel,\nthe daughter of a wealthy man in the\nSouth of France. Since the age of four\nthe girl had been obsessed with a pas\nsion for dancing. which absorbed all\nher energies, and she used to express\nevery sentiment by dance movements.\nIa the end, she literally danced herself\nto death,\nRising from her bed one night, the girl\nwent to an attic and danced for hours.\npentil a loud thud aroused the household.\nValentine was found dead on the attics\nfloor; the great exertion of dancing hav\ning caused syncope and death.\ng caused syncope and death. taken to \u2018her ROME, esoe j ave in jail. juace to Hamburg, about 400 miles.\nNe reer re eter A et ore ee RA\n\u201cWe Sell it for Less\u201d \u201cOur Furniture Makes Happy Homes\u201d\nWe undersell all other so-called cash stores because we do what we claim--sell for cash only.\nTherefore, we have a comparatively small collecting and bookkeeping force to pay\u2014we are our\nown salesmen and buyers, and our rent is a third less than other stores pay. We buy for cash, dis\ncountin< all our bills\u2014and we sell the same way. When we say we can save money for you our\nstatement is backed up by the straight facts. Come in and let us convince you by actual experi\nence that we really \u201csell it for less.\u201d Come NOW, while the best 