\ndays in jail.\nulent Pictures.\nBUILDS AIRSHIP\nTO GO 1,508 MILES\n\nCount Hopes to Win $500,000\nGerman Prize With Swift\nLAUSEANNE, Switzerland, May\nConnt Zeppelin is making rapid progress\nin the construction of his new airship\n\u201cIo. 4,\u201d Ir which he expects to go after\nthe $500,000 prize the German govern.\nment offers for a solution of the dirigi\nble balloon probiem. The craft is the\nlargest aerial vessel ever built, It is\ncigar shaped, 44 feet long, 53 feet in\ndiameter, with three motors of 140\nhorsepower each. Its prospective speed\nis forty-eight miles an hour, and it can\ntravel 1,508 miles at that rate without\na descent to recharge.\nThe ship is equipped with a complete\nwireless apparatus, and Count Zeppelin\nproposes an imitial trip from Lake Con\nstance to Hamburg, about 400 miles.\nMachine.","height":"34196","width":"26148"}}
